Cache

Cache is a system for caching data and retrieving cached data.

The default system uses a file cache for caching data. But the system through the adapter pattern is extendable to use any caching system attached to the application.

Example:

//Init The Cache
Cache::init();

$data = array('Apples', 'Oranges', 'Bananas');

//Check if cache has expired
if(Cache::hasExpired('mycache')):
     //Store The Cache
     Cache::writeCache('mycache', $data);
endif;

$data = Cache::readCache('mycache');

print_r($data);
